    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Biome: Forests, Jungles</em></p>\\n<p>This creeping vine, common on ruins and tree branches, has an unusual purple hue and broad green leaves. In summer it bears red flowers that resemble a woman in a large dress. Steeping these flowers in hot water produces a poisonous tea called Crimson Tears. A drinker must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or be blinded for [[/roll 1d4+2]] hours; during that time blood weeps from their eyes and they experience horrific visions of possible futures. After recovering, the character gains advantage on one skill check used within the next day, having glimpsed a potential outcome.</p>",
